Variable Description: You can add and manage your variables on this screen. You can use variables to perform basic arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
Are you sure you want to delete this var: Are you sure you want to delete this variable? Click confirm to proceed.
ImportDataset Descriptipon: You can import a new dataset or select your uploaded dataset from the menu and use it as a dataset within this flow.
RenameColumn Description: You can rename the specific column by selecting the target column and enter the new name.
StandardScaler Description: You can rescale the value of your dataset automatically by using scaler method. It will improve the range of your dataset.
FillNaColumn Description: You can fill NaN values in each column using “fill na column”. You can choose the method for filling, such as using the mean.
RegressionModel Description: Regression models help you predict how one variable influences another, providing valuable insights for forecasting.
ModelPrediction Description: You can obtain the models output by using your provided feature data or by generating predictions from your test set file.
SaveModel Description: You can either save your trained model to the Models page or export it to your local machine.
DataRanking Description: You can rank the data based on the selected column.
Skewness Description: Skewness is a measure of the asymmetry of the probability distribution of a real-valued random variable about its mean.
